comments.body: @bess I think that sounds right.  As part of [this ADR](https://github.com/pulibrary/pdc_describe/blob/main/architecture-decisions/0009-Additional-checksums.md), Carolyn and I tested the MD5s that come from this [S3 Python command-line tool](https://github.com/aws-samples/amazon-s3-checksum-verification) and it returns the base-64 encoded checksum, not the hexdigest.  The base-64 checksums matched during our testing, between testing with the Ruby digest module and comparing the result to the S3 Python script above.

pdc_describe.title: Review PPPL fixtures in PDC Describe production

comments.body:
@kelynch, @Twade968, and @bess, I had a chance to review the PPPL datasets and while most of it looks good, I came across a few issues, which I highlight below. The biggest concern pertains to provided DOI. See below for more details. They are listed in the order they appeared in PDC Describe Prod. I boldface the biggest issue:

[Design of an arrangement of cubic magnets for a quasi-axisymmetric stellarator experiment](https://pdc-describe-prod.princeton.edu/describe/works/39)

- Simply added sub-communities. Note that I added both Stellarators and Advanced Projects to ensure that Discovery index it in both

[Electromagnetic total-f algorithm for gyrokinetic particle-in-cell simulations of boundary plasma in XGC](https://pdc-describe-prod.princeton.edu/describe/works/41)

- **The DOI points to the journal article. We should either leave this blank or consider minting our own DataCite DOI. Note that there is no DOI through DOE/OSTI (this is a new dataset)**
- Add Theory sub-community
- Fix Amil Sharma name

[A dynamic magnetic tension force as the cause of failed solar eruptions](https://pdc-describe-prod.princeton.edu/describe/works/40)

- Add PS&T sub-community
- Added IsCitedBy for journal article
- Added another funder

[Data for "The value of fusion energy to a decarbonized United States electric grid"](https://pdc-describe-prod.princeton.edu/describe/works/44)

- **The DOI points to Zenodo, which is for code and not data**. The Zenodo DOI should be provided as a Related Objects (not sure what type though)
- Added IsCitedBy to journal article
- Add to PS&T subcommunity

[Lower Hybrid Drift Waves During Guide Field Reconnection](https://pdc-describe-prod.princeton.edu/describe/works/45)

- **Had to fix the author list as first and surnames were flipped for many. This needs to be fixed within DataSpace**
- Added to PS&T subcommunity
- Minor fix to funder contract no.

[Effects of collisional ion orbit loss on tokamak radial electric field and toroidal rotation in an L-mode plasma](https://pdc-describe-prod.princeton.edu/describe/works/46)

- **The DOI is incorrect and points to the wrong DataSpace record. Note the similar title**
- Added to Theory and Computation subcommunity
- Minor funder metadata changes

[Identification of a non-axisymmetric mode in laboratory experiments searching for standard magnetorotational instability](https://pdc-describe-prod.princeton.edu/describe/works/47)

- **The DOI doesn't point to the proper DataSpace record**
- Added to PS&T subcommunity
- Change keywords (capitalize for names)

[Source data for "Observation of Axisymmetric Standard Magnetorotational Instability in the Laboratory"](https://pdc-describe-prod.princeton.edu/describe/works/48)
- Added to PS&T subcommunity
- Added double quotes in title
- Added double quotes in description
- Added MPCC to funder list
- Change keywords (capitalize for names), acronyms in upper case

[Initial operation and data processing on a system for real-time evaluation of Thomson scattering signals on the Large Helical Device](https://pdc-describe-prod.princeton.edu/describe/works/51)

- Added to Stellarator sub-community
